HEADWORD: Incogitativity
<hw>In*cog`i*ta*tiv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quality of being incogitative; lack of thought or of the power of
thinking.</def> <rj><au>Wollaston.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

